When the axis of rotation no longer coincides with the anisotropy axis of the crystal, the rotational symmetry around the axis of rotation is broken. As a consequence, only a finite number of fixed points exists. For an autonomous system on the unit sphere such as the LLG equation with time-independent effective field, it follows from the Poincare index theorem[11, 10] then that the number of (un)stable fixed points minus the number of saddles must be equal to two.
